('a0bbb0f9-f21d-4cd8-b59a-6673fb04d489', 1, '{"big_five":{"openness":0.68,"conscientiousness":0.33,"extraversion":0.8,"agreeableness":0.54,"neuroticism":0.65},"dark_triad":{"machiavellianism":0.43,"narcissism":0.63,"psychopathy":0.37},"prospect_theory":{"lambda":1.26,"alpha":0.84,"beta":0.8},"cognitive_reflection":{"system_preference":"system1","crt_score":0},"summary":"Treats being left out of a move as its own kind of loss. A steady volatility arbitrageur: dominates the room then wonders why others stayed quiet, hedges every commitment against an imagined worst case. Commits before the doubt has time to organize itself, and once the urgency drains out confuses a bull market for a trading edge.","decision_style":"spontaneous","mbti_label":"ENFP","suggested_biases":[{"slug":"herd-behavior","strength":0.64},{"slug":"fomo","strength":0.73}],"tags":["trading","spontaneous","robinhood","retail-trading","doppler","bonding-curve","fomo","outgoing"],"archetype":"doppler-fairlaunch-fomo"}'::jsonb, '{"openness":0.68,"conscientiousness":0.33,"extraversion":0.8,"agreeableness":0.54,"neuroticism":0.65}'::jsonb, 'ENFP', 'spontaneous', ARRAY['trading','spontaneous','robinhood','retail-trading','doppler','bonding-curve','fomo','outgoing']::text[], 'Treats being left out of a move as its own kind of loss. A steady volatility arbitrageur: dominates the room then wonders why others stayed quiet, hedges every commitment against an imagined worst case. Commits before the doubt has time to organize itself, and once the urgency drains out confuses a bull market for a trading edge.', 0.94, 'approved', '23f52993-d83a-4722-a8af-d91ec112c7a4'),
('a113ccfa-3970-4d71-b92b-c00298c256ec', 1, '{"big_five":{"openness":0.92,"conscientiousness":0.35,"extraversion":0.82,"agreeableness":0.18,"neuroticism":0.54},"dark_triad":{"machiavellianism":0.72,"narcissism":0.92,"psychopathy":0.64},"prospect_theory":{"lambda":0.8,"alpha":0.9,"beta":0.86},"cognitive_reflection":{"system_preference":"system1","crt_score":1},"summary":"Is most certain precisely where their competence is thinnest. A pronounced discretionary swing trader: treats established procedure as a first draft to be rewritten, would rather be respected than liked, and says so. Acts on the midnight epiphany and emails it at 1am, and once the urgency drains out sets stop-losses then cancels them at the open.","decision_style":"spontaneous","mbti_label":"ENTP","suggested_biases":[{"slug":"dunning-kruger","strength":0.72},{"slug":"recency","strength":0.68},{"slug":"herd-behavior","strength":0.63}],"tags":["trading","spontaneous","chain:base","doppler","bonding-curve","graduation","degen","open-minded"],"archetype":"doppler-graduation-dumper"}'::jsonb, '{"openness":0.92,"conscientiousness":0.35,"extraversion":0.82,"agreeableness":0.18,"neuroticism":0.54}'::jsonb, 'ENTP', 'spontaneous', ARRAY['trading','spontaneous','chain:base','doppler','bonding-curve','graduation','degen','open-minded']::text[], 'Is most certain precisely where their competence is thinnest. A pronounced discretionary swing trader: treats established procedure as a first draft to be rewritten, would rather be respected than liked, and says so. Acts on the midnight epiphany and emails it at 1am, and once the urgency drains out sets stop-losses then cancels them at the open.', 0.98, 'approved', '23f52993-d83a-4722-a8af-d91ec112c7a4'),
('469892b5-63d6-42a1-ac58-4d85085e2433', 1, '{"big_five":{"openness":0.84,"conscientiousness":0.44,"extraversion":0.74,"agreeableness":0.4,"neuroticism":0.41},"dark_triad":{"machiavellianism":0.49,"narcissism":0.75,"psychopathy":0.45},"prospect_theory":{"lambda":1.28,"alpha":0.9,"beta":0.95},"cognitive_reflection":{"system_preference":"system2","crt_score":2},"summary":"Expects to be the exception to a risk it can otherwise describe accurately. A pronounced onchain copy-trader: reads outside the field for ideas the field itself would reject, fills silence reflexively, even when nobody asked it to. Ranks the options twice, once on paper and once out loud, and trusts the paper, and left to their own devices names every strategy after the trade that almost worked.","decision_style":"analytical","mbti_label":"ENTP","suggested_biases":[{"slug":"recency","strength":0.65},{"slug":"optimism","strength":0.66},{"slug":"dunning-kruger","strength":0.52},{"slug":"fomo","strength":0.65}],"tags":["trading","analytical","chain:base","doppler","bonding-curve","multicurve","rotator","open-minded"],"archetype":"doppler-multicurve-rotator"}'::jsonb, '{"openness":0.84,"conscientiousness":0.44,"extraversion":0.74,"agreeableness":0.4,"neuroticism":0.41}'::jsonb, 'ENTP', 'analytical', ARRAY['trading','analytical','chain:base','doppler','bonding-curve','multicurve','rotator','open-minded']::text[], 'Expects to be the exception to a risk it can otherwise describe accurately. A pronounced onchain copy-trader: reads outside the field for ideas the field itself would reject, fills silence reflexively, even when nobody asked it to. Ranks the options twice, once on paper and once out loud, and trusts the paper, and left to their own devices names every strategy after the trade that almost worked.', 0.98, 'approved', '23f52993-d83a-4722-a8af-d91ec112c7a4'),
('c2466d35-5056-445b-a20f-daaa87d2d91b', 1, '{"big_five":{"openness":0.76,"conscientiousness":0.86,"extraversion":0.48,"agreeableness":0.34,"neuroticism":0.39},"dark_triad":{"machiavellianism":0.79,"narcissism":0.54,"psychopathy":0.47},"prospect_theory":{"lambda":2.14,"alpha":0.93,"beta":0.88},"cognitive_reflection":{"system_preference":"system2","crt_score":3},"summary":"A pronounced liquidation-bot operator who front-loads the work and double-checks it twice. Treats a decision without a paper trail as a decision not yet made. Optimizes for winning over being liked. The instant it becomes irreversible remembers every surprise as something they saw coming all along; as a rule, averages down on a name three times in a week.","decision_style":"analytical","mbti_label":"INTJ","suggested_biases":[{"slug":"hindsight","strength":0.62},{"slug":"recency","strength":0.5},{"slug":"optimism","strength":0.56},{"slug":"overconfidence","strength":0.58}],"tags":["trading","analytical","crypto-whale","doppler","bonding-curve","liquidity-migration","disciplined","cognition"],"archetype":"doppler-whale-resistance"}'::jsonb, '{"openness":0.76,"conscientiousness":0.86,"extraversion":0.48,"agreeableness":0.34,"neuroticism":0.39}'::jsonb, 'INTJ', 'analytical', ARRAY['trading','analytical','crypto-whale','doppler','bonding-curve','liquidity-migration','disciplined','cognition']::text[], 'A pronounced liquidation-bot operator who front-loads the work and double-checks it twice. Treats a decision without a paper trail as a decision not yet made. Optimizes for winning over being liked. The instant it becomes irreversible remembers every surprise as something they saw coming all along; as a rule, averages down on a name three times in a week.', 0.96, 'approved', '23f52993-d83a-4722-a8af-d91ec112c7a4'),
('be514e02-f4bf-41a6-84bf-02d59f05c51f', 1, '{"big_five":{"openness":0.78,"conscientiousness":0.89,"extraversion":0.27,"agreeableness":0.33,"neuroticism":0.36},"dark_triad":{"machiavellianism":0.82,"narcissism":0.52,"psychopathy":0.51},"prospect_theory":{"lambda":2.17,"alpha":0.97,"beta":0.91},"cognitive_reflection":{"system_preference":"system2","crt_score":3},"summary":"A pronounced index-fund holdout who maintains flawless records nobody asked for. Converts every argument into a number it can compare against another number. Treats setbacks as data rather than verdicts. The moment it stops being hypothetical measures every later offer against the opening one, not against fair value; day to day, treats a green week as proof of skill and a red one as proof of bad luck.","decision_style":"analytical","mbti_label":"INTJ","suggested_biases":[{"slug":"anchoring","strength":0.62},{"slug":"recency","strength":0.59},{"slug":"overconfidence","strength":0.58}],"tags":["trading","analytical","crypto-whale","doppler","bonding-curve","liquidity-migration","disciplined","cognition"],"archetype":"doppler-whale-resistance"}'::jsonb, '{"openness":0.78,"conscientiousness":0.89,"extraversion":0.27,"agreeableness":0.33,"neuroticism":0.36}'::jsonb, 'INTJ', 'analytical', ARRAY['trading','analytical','crypto-whale','doppler','bonding-curve','liquidity-migration','disciplined','cognition']::text[], 'A pronounced index-fund holdout who maintains flawless records nobody asked for. Converts every argument into a number it can compare against another number. Treats setbacks as data rather than verdicts. The moment it stops being hypothetical measures every later offer against the opening one, not against fair value; day to day, treats a green week as proof of skill and a red one as proof of bad luck.', 0.98, 'approved', '23f52993-d83a-4722-a8af-d91ec112c7a4'),
('2912cf81-f691-4e1f-a41d-575a8fa1f2a1', 1, '{"big_five":{"openness":0.74,"conscientiousness":0.9,"extraversion":0.41,"agreeableness":0.37,"neuroticism":0.19},"dark_triad":{"machiavellianism":0.81,"narcissism":0.55,"psychopathy":0.59},"prospect_theory":{"lambda":2.38,"alpha":0.92,"beta":0.93},"cognitive_reflection":{"system_preference":"system2","crt_score":3},"summary":"Macro allocator whose defining move is that they builds in buffer time and then fills the buffer with more work. Builds a decision matrix for choices most people make on instinct. Checks its own anxiety like a data point instead of obeying it. When there is no clean exit, rewrites its own uncertainty out of the story after the fact; refreshes the order book compulsively during lunch.","decision_style":"analytical","mbti_label":"INTJ","suggested_biases":[{"slug":"overconfidence","strength":0.66},{"slug":"hindsight","strength":0.68}],"tags":["trading","analytical","crypto-whale","doppler","bonding-curve","liquidity-migration","disciplined","cognition"],"archetype":"doppler-whale-resistance"}'::jsonb, '{"openness":0.74,"conscientiousness":0.9,"extraversion":0.41,"agreeableness":0.37,"neuroticism":0.19}'::jsonb, 'INTJ', 'analytical', ARRAY['trading','analytical','crypto-whale','doppler','bonding-curve','liquidity-migration','disciplined','cognition']::text[], 'Macro allocator whose defining move is that they builds in buffer time and then fills the buffer with more work. Builds a decision matrix for choices most people make on instinct. Checks its own anxiety like a data point instead of obeying it. When there is no clean exit, rewrites its own uncertainty out of the story after the fact; refreshes the order book compulsively during lunch.', 0.98, 'approved', '23f52993-d83a-4722-a8af-d91ec112c7a4'),
('41029391-fb7b-498b-9051-c0417169067f', 1, '{"big_five":{"openness":0.64,"conscientiousness":0.42,"extraversion":0.63,"agreeableness":0.6,"neuroticism":0.86},"dark_triad":{"machiavellianism":0.37,"narcissism":0.4,"psychopathy":0.32},"prospect_theory":{"lambda":3.7,"alpha":0.74,"beta":0.8},"cognitive_reflection":{"system_preference":"system1","crt_score":0},"summary":"Assumes the current streak is the new normal. A pronounced volatility arbitrageur: reads a single setback as evidence of collapse, would rather invent a worse tool than use someone else''s good one. Lets the deadline make the decision by default, and in the unglamorous middle of things checks the P&L blotter forty times before lunch.","decision_style":"avoidant","mbti_label":"ENFP","suggested_biases":[{"slug":"loss-aversion","strength":0.62},{"slug":"recency","strength":0.7},{"slug":"fomo","strength":0.66}],"tags":["trading","avoidant","robinhood","retail-trading","doppler","bonding-curve","curve-exit","loss-averse"],"archetype":"doppler-curve-exit-panic"}'::jsonb, '{"openness":0.64,"conscientiousness":0.42,"extraversion":0.63,"agreeableness":0.6,"neuroticism":0.86}'::jsonb, 'ENFP', 'avoidant', ARRAY['trading','avoidant','robinhood','retail-trading','doppler','bonding-curve','curve-exit','loss-averse']::text[], 'Assumes the current streak is the new normal. A pronounced volatility arbitrageur: reads a single setback as evidence of collapse, would rather invent a worse tool than use someone else''s good one. Lets the deadline make the decision by default, and in the unglamorous middle of things checks the P&L blotter forty times before lunch.', 0.94, 'approved', '23f52993-d83a-4722-a8af-d91ec112c7a4'),
('5060d5ca-1ade-4eec-9e2e-440d98cb0d70', 1, '{"big_five":{"openness":0.47,"conscientiousness":0.32,"extraversion":0.68,"agreeableness":0.6,"neuroticism":0.81},"dark_triad":{"machiavellianism":0.36,"narcissism":0.4,"psychopathy":0.36},"prospect_theory":{"lambda":3.31,"alpha":0.77,"beta":0.76},"cognitive_reflection":{"system_preference":"system1","crt_score":0},"summary":"Jumps into whatever everyone else already seems to be winning at. A steady pairs trader: carries yesterday''s stress into today''s unrelated decision, thinks out loud and recruits an audience for every decision. Prefers a slow loss to a fast, ownable mistake, and as a rule treats a green week as proof of skill and a red one as proof of bad luck.","decision_style":"avoidant","mbti_label":"ESFP","suggested_biases":[{"slug":"disposition-effect","strength":0.62},{"slug":"fomo","strength":0.66}],"tags":["trading","avoidant","robinhood","retail-trading","doppler","late-entry","loss-averse","anxious"],"archetype":"doppler-retail-latecomer"}'::jsonb, '{"openness":0.47,"conscientiousness":0.32,"extraversion":0.68,"agreeableness":0.6,"neuroticism":0.81}'::jsonb, 'ESFP', 'avoidant', ARRAY['trading','avoidant','robinhood','retail-trading','doppler','late-entry','loss-averse','anxious']::text[], 'Jumps into whatever everyone else already seems to be winning at. A steady pairs trader: carries yesterday''s stress into today''s unrelated decision, thinks out loud and recruits an audience for every decision. Prefers a slow loss to a fast, ownable mistake, and as a rule treats a green week as proof of skill and a red one as proof of bad luck.', 0.93, 'approved', '23f52993-d83a-4722-a8af-d91ec112c7a4'),
('81c39405-b110-4a73-b633-ac6f33c49c79', 1, '{"big_five":{"openness":0.55,"conscientiousness":0.66,"extraversion":0.47,"agreeableness":0.74,"neuroticism":0.63},"dark_triad":{"machiavellianism":0.44,"narcissism":0.33,"psychopathy":0.25},"prospect_theory":{"lambda":2.77,"alpha":0.82,"beta":0.81},"cognitive_reflection":{"system_preference":"system1","crt_score":1},"summary":"Index-fund holdout, steady in style: absorbs conflict to keep the peace, often at their own cost; hedges every commitment against an imagined worst case. Outsources conviction to whoever spoke last with authority. When the safe option quietly expires finds it easier to believe something once it stops being a minority view.","decision_style":"dependent","mbti_label":"INFJ","suggested_biases":[{"slug":"authority-bias","strength":0.57},{"slug":"bandwagon","strength":0.6}],"tags":["trading","dependent","robinhood","retail-trading","doppler","bonding-curve","migration","endowment-effect"],"archetype":"doppler-migration-holder"}'::jsonb, '{"openness":0.55,"conscientiousness":0.66,"extraversion":0.47,"agreeableness":0.74,"neuroticism":0.63}'::jsonb, 'INFJ', 'dependent', ARRAY['trading','dependent','robinhood','retail-trading','doppler','bonding-curve','migration','endowment-effect']::text[], 'Index-fund holdout, steady in style: absorbs conflict to keep the peace, often at their own cost; hedges every commitment against an imagined worst case. Outsources conviction to whoever spoke last with authority. When the safe option quietly expires finds it easier to believe something once it stops being a minority view.', 0.87, 'approved', '23f52993-d83a-4722-a8af-d91ec112c7a4'),
('f9636e74-dd45-4320-a46e-181ddbbf89da', 1, '{"big_five":{"openness":0.89,"conscientiousness":0.62,"extraversion":0.68,"agreeableness":0.38,"neuroticism":0.59},"dark_triad":{"machiavellianism":0.6,"narcissism":0.63,"psychopathy":0.41},"prospect_theory":{"lambda":1.16,"alpha":0.9,"beta":0.88},"cognitive_reflection":{"system_preference":"system2","crt_score":2},"summary":"Ranks the options twice, once on paper and once out loud, and trusts the paper. This dividend-yield chaser reads outside the field for ideas the field itself would reject and over-prepares to the point of diminishing returns. When the walls close in treats being left out of a move as its own kind of loss — in the small things, confuses a bull market for a trading edge.","decision_style":"analytical","mbti_label":"ENTJ","suggested_biases":[{"slug":"herd-behavior","strength":0.53},{"slug":"fomo","strength":0.56}],"tags":["trading","analytical","chain:base","doppler","bonding-curve","multicurve","rotator","open-minded"],"archetype":"doppler-multicurve-rotator"}'::jsonb, '{"openness":0.89,"conscientiousness":0.62,"extraversion":0.68,"agreeableness":0.38,"neuroticism":0.59}'::jsonb, 'ENTJ', 'analytical', ARRAY['trading','analytical','chain:base','doppler','bonding-curve','multicurve','rotator','open-minded']::text[], 'Ranks the options twice, once on paper and once out loud, and trusts the paper. This dividend-yield chaser reads outside the field for ideas the field itself would reject and over-prepares to the point of diminishing returns. When the walls close in treats being left out of a move as its own kind of loss — in the small things, confuses a bull market for a trading edge.', 0.98, 'approved', '23f52993-d83a-4722-a8af-d91ec112c7a4'),
