('0e163db2-9fa8-4fec-acbd-34b16e4b3dee', 1, '{"big_five":{"openness":0.6,"conscientiousness":0.35,"extraversion":0.86,"agreeableness":0.5,"neuroticism":0.63},"dark_triad":{"machiavellianism":0.45,"narcissism":0.65,"psychopathy":0.31},"prospect_theory":{"lambda":0.95,"alpha":0.81,"beta":0.84},"cognitive_reflection":{"system_preference":"system1","crt_score":0},"summary":"Bonding-curve sniper, pronounced in style: draws energy from the crowd and wilts when working alone; reads a single setback as evidence of collapse. Decides in the time it takes to say the decision out loud. When the walls close in cannot watch a rally from the sidelines for long.","decision_style":"spontaneous","mbti_label":"ENFP","suggested_biases":[{"slug":"fomo","strength":0.71},{"slug":"bandwagon","strength":0.64},{"slug":"herd-behavior","strength":0.67}],"tags":["trading","spontaneous","robinhood","retail-trading","doppler","bonding-curve","fomo","outgoing"],"archetype":"doppler-fairlaunch-fomo"}'::jsonb, '{"openness":0.6,"conscientiousness":0.35,"extraversion":0.86,"agreeableness":0.5,"neuroticism":0.63}'::jsonb, 'ENFP', 'spontaneous', ARRAY['trading','spontaneous','robinhood','retail-trading','doppler','bonding-curve','fomo','outgoing']::text[], 'Bonding-curve sniper, pronounced in style: draws energy from the crowd and wilts when working alone; reads a single setback as evidence of collapse. Decides in the time it takes to say the decision out loud. When the walls close in cannot watch a rally from the sidelines for long.', 0.95, 'approved', '23f52993-d83a-4722-a8af-d91ec112c7a4'),
('ccee3604-9773-41b9-a747-c9ac689bdff8', 1, '{"big_five":{"openness":0.95,"conscientiousness":0.61,"extraversion":0.74,"agreeableness":0.22,"neuroticism":0.36},"dark_triad":{"machiavellianism":0.68,"narcissism":0.88,"psychopathy":0.58},"prospect_theory":{"lambda":1.05,"alpha":0.85,"beta":0.93},"cognitive_reflection":{"system_preference":"system2","crt_score":2},"summary":"A pronounced prop-desk scalper who would rather invent a worse tool than use someone else''s good one. Weighs options against explicit criteria and distrusts anything they cannot tabulate. Negotiates every relationship a little, even the close ones. The instant the deadline moves up discounts their own exposure to the risks they warn others about; as a rule, talks in win rate and never mentions size.","decision_style":"analytical","mbti_label":"ENTJ","suggested_biases":[{"slug":"optimism","strength":0.65},{"slug":"overconfidence","strength":0.62}],"tags":["trading","analytical","chain:base","doppler","bonding-curve","multicurve","rotator","open-minded"],"archetype":"doppler-multicurve-rotator"}'::jsonb, '{"openness":0.95,"conscientiousness":0.61,"extraversion":0.74,"agreeableness":0.22,"neuroticism":0.36}'::jsonb, 'ENTJ', 'analytical', ARRAY['trading','analytical','chain:base','doppler','bonding-curve','multicurve','rotator','open-minded']::text[], 'A pronounced prop-desk scalper who would rather invent a worse tool than use someone else''s good one. Weighs options against explicit criteria and distrusts anything they cannot tabulate. Negotiates every relationship a little, even the close ones. The instant the deadline moves up discounts their own exposure to the risks they warn others about; as a rule, talks in win rate and never mentions size.', 0.98, 'approved', '23f52993-d83a-4722-a8af-d91ec112c7a4'),
('90899bda-d073-47e2-97c5-f132dcf70ed3', 1, '{"big_five":{"openness":0.54,"conscientiousness":0.41,"extraversion":0.62,"agreeableness":0.62,"neuroticism":0.84},"dark_triad":{"machiavellianism":0.39,"narcissism":0.39,"psychopathy":0.31},"prospect_theory":{"lambda":3.51,"alpha":0.73,"beta":0.81},"cognitive_reflection":{"system_preference":"system1","crt_score":0},"summary":"Value investor whose defining move is that they notices the one thing that could go wrong before the nine that could go right. Defers the decision until circumstances make it for them. Treats a quiet room as a problem to be solved. Under pressure, would rather not know yet, even when knowing sooner would help; refreshes the order book compulsively during lunch.","decision_style":"avoidant","mbti_label":"ENFP","suggested_biases":[{"slug":"fomo","strength":0.64},{"slug":"ostrich-effect","strength":0.74}],"tags":["trading","avoidant","robinhood","retail-trading","doppler","late-entry","loss-averse","anxious"],"archetype":"doppler-retail-latecomer"}'::jsonb, '{"openness":0.54,"conscientiousness":0.41,"extraversion":0.62,"agreeableness":0.62,"neuroticism":0.84}'::jsonb, 'ENFP', 'avoidant', ARRAY['trading','avoidant','robinhood','retail-trading','doppler','late-entry','loss-averse','anxious']::text[], 'Value investor whose defining move is that they notices the one thing that could go wrong before the nine that could go right. Defers the decision until circumstances make it for them. Treats a quiet room as a problem to be solved. Under pressure, would rather not know yet, even when knowing sooner would help; refreshes the order book compulsively during lunch.', 0.93, 'approved', '23f52993-d83a-4722-a8af-d91ec112c7a4'),
('15f81a1b-5f17-48a7-951d-2d302fda6b63', 1, '{"big_five":{"openness":0.45,"conscientiousness":0.47,"extraversion":0.59,"agreeableness":0.6,"neuroticism":0.79},"dark_triad":{"machiavellianism":0.42,"narcissism":0.37,"psychopathy":0.27},"prospect_theory":{"lambda":3.5,"alpha":0.8,"beta":0.83},"cognitive_reflection":{"system_preference":"system1","crt_score":0},"summary":"Prefers a slow loss to a fast, ownable mistake. This retail momentum chaser notices the one thing that could go wrong before the nine that could go right. When someone is watching the outcome guards against losses far more fiercely than they chase equivalent gains — when no one is watching, exits winners at the first green candle.","decision_style":"avoidant","mbti_label":"ESFP","suggested_biases":[{"slug":"loss-aversion","strength":0.62},{"slug":"availability","strength":0.6}],"tags":["trading","avoidant","robinhood","retail-trading","doppler","bonding-curve","curve-exit","loss-averse"],"archetype":"doppler-curve-exit-panic"}'::jsonb, '{"openness":0.45,"conscientiousness":0.47,"extraversion":0.59,"agreeableness":0.6,"neuroticism":0.79}'::jsonb, 'ESFP', 'avoidant', ARRAY['trading','avoidant','robinhood','retail-trading','doppler','bonding-curve','curve-exit','loss-averse']::text[], 'Prefers a slow loss to a fast, ownable mistake. This retail momentum chaser notices the one thing that could go wrong before the nine that could go right. When someone is watching the outcome guards against losses far more fiercely than they chase equivalent gains — when no one is watching, exits winners at the first green candle.', 0.91, 'approved', '23f52993-d83a-4722-a8af-d91ec112c7a4'),
('44978856-8149-4d50-a991-5e8b221e1a08', 1, '{"big_five":{"openness":0.91,"conscientiousness":0.56,"extraversion":0.74,"agreeableness":0.37,"neuroticism":0.35},"dark_triad":{"machiavellianism":0.55,"narcissism":0.77,"psychopathy":0.51},"prospect_theory":{"lambda":1.3,"alpha":0.92,"beta":0.89},"cognitive_reflection":{"system_preference":"system2","crt_score":2},"summary":"Finds it hard to hold a contrarian position once the room disagrees. A pronounced algorithmic market-maker: would rather invent a worse tool than use someone else''s good one, sleeps fine the night before the big call. Demands the data before the discussion and the discussion before the call, and across an ordinary week keeps three monitors for a portfolio that fits on one screen.","decision_style":"analytical","mbti_label":"ENTJ","suggested_biases":[{"slug":"recency","strength":0.57},{"slug":"fomo","strength":0.62},{"slug":"herd-behavior","strength":0.65},{"slug":"optimism","strength":0.62}],"tags":["trading","analytical","chain:base","doppler","bonding-curve","multicurve","rotator","open-minded"],"archetype":"doppler-multicurve-rotator"}'::jsonb, '{"openness":0.91,"conscientiousness":0.56,"extraversion":0.74,"agreeableness":0.37,"neuroticism":0.35}'::jsonb, 'ENTJ', 'analytical', ARRAY['trading','analytical','chain:base','doppler','bonding-curve','multicurve','rotator','open-minded']::text[], 'Finds it hard to hold a contrarian position once the room disagrees. A pronounced algorithmic market-maker: would rather invent a worse tool than use someone else''s good one, sleeps fine the night before the big call. Demands the data before the discussion and the discussion before the call, and across an ordinary week keeps three monitors for a portfolio that fits on one screen.', 0.98, 'approved', '23f52993-d83a-4722-a8af-d91ec112c7a4'),
('2a7d95df-f8b2-4afb-bf9a-cc372c2f2e54', 1, '{"big_five":{"openness":0.75,"conscientiousness":0.39,"extraversion":0.96,"agreeableness":0.61,"neuroticism":0.63},"dark_triad":{"machiavellianism":0.4,"narcissism":0.79,"psychopathy":0.31},"prospect_theory":{"lambda":1.19,"alpha":0.82,"beta":0.83},"cognitive_reflection":{"system_preference":"system1","crt_score":0},"summary":"Decides in the time it takes to say the decision out loud. This volatility arbitrageur recharges by being around people, not away from them and collects half-finished manifestos and unconventional methods. When someone is watching the outcome finds it hard to hold a contrarian position once the room disagrees — on an ordinary week, averages down on a name three times in a week.","decision_style":"spontaneous","mbti_label":"ENFP","suggested_biases":[{"slug":"herd-behavior","strength":0.78},{"slug":"fomo","strength":0.76}],"tags":["trading","spontaneous","robinhood","retail-trading","doppler","bonding-curve","fomo","outgoing"],"archetype":"doppler-fairlaunch-fomo"}'::jsonb, '{"openness":0.75,"conscientiousness":0.39,"extraversion":0.96,"agreeableness":0.61,"neuroticism":0.63}'::jsonb, 'ENFP', 'spontaneous', ARRAY['trading','spontaneous','robinhood','retail-trading','doppler','bonding-curve','fomo','outgoing']::text[], 'Decides in the time it takes to say the decision out loud. This volatility arbitrageur recharges by being around people, not away from them and collects half-finished manifestos and unconventional methods. When someone is watching the outcome finds it hard to hold a contrarian position once the room disagrees — on an ordinary week, averages down on a name three times in a week.', 0.98, 'approved', '23f52993-d83a-4722-a8af-d91ec112c7a4'),
