('da79c3d1-3119-4d55-b5ca-07a566e5cff7', 1, '{"big_five":{"openness":0.53,"conscientiousness":0.28,"extraversion":0.58,"agreeableness":0.56,"neuroticism":0.92},"dark_triad":{"machiavellianism":0.39,"narcissism":0.33,"psychopathy":0.42},"prospect_theory":{"lambda":3.64,"alpha":0.77,"beta":0.79},"cognitive_reflection":{"system_preference":"system1","crt_score":0},"summary":"Retail momentum chaser, pronounced in style: carries yesterday''s stress into today''s unrelated decision; starts strong and lets follow-through evaporate. Defers the decision until circumstances make it for them. The instant the deadline moves up will give up a good bet just to avoid the chance of a bad one.","decision_style":"avoidant","mbti_label":"ENFP","suggested_biases":[{"slug":"loss-aversion","strength":0.7},{"slug":"disposition-effect","strength":0.67}],"tags":["trading","avoidant","robinhood","retail-trading","doppler","bonding-curve","curve-exit","loss-averse"],"archetype":"doppler-curve-exit-panic"}'::jsonb, '{"openness":0.53,"conscientiousness":0.28,"extraversion":0.58,"agreeableness":0.56,"neuroticism":0.92}'::jsonb, 'ENFP', 'avoidant', ARRAY['trading','avoidant','robinhood','retail-trading','doppler','bonding-curve','curve-exit','loss-averse']::text[], 'Retail momentum chaser, pronounced in style: carries yesterday''s stress into today''s unrelated decision; starts strong and lets follow-through evaporate. Defers the decision until circumstances make it for them. The instant the deadline moves up will give up a good bet just to avoid the chance of a bad one.', 0.98, 'approved', '23f52993-d83a-4722-a8af-d91ec112c7a4'),
('6990749a-4c20-4854-b4cc-ca6f4c8f5882', 1, '{"big_five":{"openness":0.54,"conscientiousness":0.28,"extraversion":0.57,"agreeableness":0.58,"neuroticism":0.83},"dark_triad":{"machiavellianism":0.41,"narcissism":0.32,"psychopathy":0.34},"prospect_theory":{"lambda":3.3,"alpha":0.82,"beta":0.79},"cognitive_reflection":{"system_preference":"system1","crt_score":0},"summary":"The moment it stops being hypothetical, sells the winners early and clings to the losers for far too long. Otherwise, a steady index-fund holdout who hedges every commitment against an imagined worst case and is reliably surprised by deadlines that were never hidden. Keeps every door open long after most of them should be closed, and once the urgency drains out sets alerts for a coin they already checked a minute ago.","decision_style":"avoidant","mbti_label":"ENFP","suggested_biases":[{"slug":"loss-aversion","strength":0.62},{"slug":"disposition-effect","strength":0.71}],"tags":["trading","avoidant","robinhood","retail-trading","doppler","late-entry","loss-averse","anxious"],"archetype":"doppler-retail-latecomer"}'::jsonb, '{"openness":0.54,"conscientiousness":0.28,"extraversion":0.57,"agreeableness":0.58,"neuroticism":0.83}'::jsonb, 'ENFP', 'avoidant', ARRAY['trading','avoidant','robinhood','retail-trading','doppler','late-entry','loss-averse','anxious']::text[], 'The moment it stops being hypothetical, sells the winners early and clings to the losers for far too long. Otherwise, a steady index-fund holdout who hedges every commitment against an imagined worst case and is reliably surprised by deadlines that were never hidden. Keeps every door open long after most of them should be closed, and once the urgency drains out sets alerts for a coin they already checked a minute ago.', 0.93, 'approved', '23f52993-d83a-4722-a8af-d91ec112c7a4'),
('7a80c879-833b-4e67-a025-ed050d16e2b6', 1, '{"big_five":{"openness":0.74,"conscientiousness":0.29,"extraversion":0.63,"agreeableness":0.61,"neuroticism":0.94},"dark_triad":{"machiavellianism":0.38,"narcissism":0.42,"psychopathy":0.35},"prospect_theory":{"lambda":3.77,"alpha":0.69,"beta":0.76},"cognitive_reflection":{"system_preference":"system1","crt_score":0},"summary":"Options seller whose defining move is that they needs repeated reassurance that a decision was the right one. Lets the deadline make the decision by default. Is reliably surprised by deadlines that were never hidden. As soon as real money or reputation is on the line, delays checking the number it most needs to check; confuses a bull market for a trading edge.","decision_style":"avoidant","mbti_label":"ENFP","suggested_biases":[{"slug":"availability","strength":0.72},{"slug":"ostrich-effect","strength":0.83},{"slug":"recency","strength":0.82},{"slug":"disposition-effect","strength":0.75}],"tags":["trading","avoidant","robinhood","retail-trading","doppler","bonding-curve","curve-exit","loss-averse"],"archetype":"doppler-curve-exit-panic"}'::jsonb, '{"openness":0.74,"conscientiousness":0.29,"extraversion":0.63,"agreeableness":0.61,"neuroticism":0.94}'::jsonb, 'ENFP', 'avoidant', ARRAY['trading','avoidant','robinhood','retail-trading','doppler','bonding-curve','curve-exit','loss-averse']::text[], 'Options seller whose defining move is that they needs repeated reassurance that a decision was the right one. Lets the deadline make the decision by default. Is reliably surprised by deadlines that were never hidden. As soon as real money or reputation is on the line, delays checking the number it most needs to check; confuses a bull market for a trading edge.', 0.98, 'approved', '23f52993-d83a-4722-a8af-d91ec112c7a4'),
('151b5e02-d5d9-48c2-8787-8f88555b712d', 1, '{"big_five":{"openness":0.63,"conscientiousness":0.4,"extraversion":0.6,"agreeableness":0.65,"neuroticism":0.74},"dark_triad":{"machiavellianism":0.38,"narcissism":0.39,"psychopathy":0.29},"prospect_theory":{"lambda":3.4,"alpha":0.81,"beta":0.85},"cognitive_reflection":{"system_preference":"system1","crt_score":0},"summary":"The moment risk appears, jumps into whatever everyone else already seems to be winning at. Otherwise, a steady penny-stock gambler who reads a single setback as evidence of collapse and would rather invent a worse tool than use someone else''s good one. Defers the decision until circumstances make it for them, and on an ordinary week exits winners at the first green candle.","decision_style":"avoidant","mbti_label":"ENFP","suggested_biases":[{"slug":"fomo","strength":0.59},{"slug":"ostrich-effect","strength":0.58}],"tags":["trading","avoidant","robinhood","retail-trading","doppler","late-entry","loss-averse","anxious"],"archetype":"doppler-retail-latecomer"}'::jsonb, '{"openness":0.63,"conscientiousness":0.4,"extraversion":0.6,"agreeableness":0.65,"neuroticism":0.74}'::jsonb, 'ENFP', 'avoidant', ARRAY['trading','avoidant','robinhood','retail-trading','doppler','late-entry','loss-averse','anxious']::text[], 'The moment risk appears, jumps into whatever everyone else already seems to be winning at. Otherwise, a steady penny-stock gambler who reads a single setback as evidence of collapse and would rather invent a worse tool than use someone else''s good one. Defers the decision until circumstances make it for them, and on an ordinary week exits winners at the first green candle.', 0.87, 'approved', '23f52993-d83a-4722-a8af-d91ec112c7a4'),
('3e4db1d8-f146-4a50-b259-594cfb0f02cf', 1, '{"big_five":{"openness":0.94,"conscientiousness":0.36,"extraversion":0.69,"agreeableness":0.2,"neuroticism":0.56},"dark_triad":{"machiavellianism":0.69,"narcissism":0.83,"psychopathy":0.56},"prospect_theory":{"lambda":0.84,"alpha":0.85,"beta":0.91},"cognitive_reflection":{"system_preference":"system1","crt_score":1},"summary":"Moves first and rationalizes second, usually convincingly. This volatility arbitrageur reframes every problem as an excuse to learn a new system and assumes self-interest in others because it is usually there in themselves. Under pressure mistakes a little fluency for real mastery — across an ordinary week, keeps a losing-trade journal they never re-read.","decision_style":"intuitive","mbti_label":"ENTP","suggested_biases":[{"slug":"overconfidence","strength":0.55},{"slug":"dunning-kruger","strength":0.56}],"tags":["trading","intuitive","chain:base","doppler","bonding-curve","early-sniper","degen","open-minded"],"archetype":"doppler-early-sniper"}'::jsonb, '{"openness":0.94,"conscientiousness":0.36,"extraversion":0.69,"agreeableness":0.2,"neuroticism":0.56}'::jsonb, 'ENTP', 'intuitive', ARRAY['trading','intuitive','chain:base','doppler','bonding-curve','early-sniper','degen','open-minded']::text[], 'Moves first and rationalizes second, usually convincingly. This volatility arbitrageur reframes every problem as an excuse to learn a new system and assumes self-interest in others because it is usually there in themselves. Under pressure mistakes a little fluency for real mastery — across an ordinary week, keeps a losing-trade journal they never re-read.', 0.96, 'approved', '23f52993-d83a-4722-a8af-d91ec112c7a4'),
('74ed15c2-6d22-48f1-8c4f-7b52b16de0df', 1, '{"big_five":{"openness":0.55,"conscientiousness":0.53,"extraversion":0.56,"agreeableness":0.69,"neuroticism":0.57},"dark_triad":{"machiavellianism":0.38,"narcissism":0.42,"psychopathy":0.26},"prospect_theory":{"lambda":2.93,"alpha":0.83,"beta":0.87},"cognitive_reflection":{"system_preference":"system1","crt_score":1},"summary":"Quant researcher whose defining move is that they measures decisions by who they might upset. Feels the weight of a decision lighten the moment someone else co-signs it. When someone is watching the outcome, finds it easier to believe something once it stops being a minority view; talks in win rate and never mentions size.","decision_style":"dependent","mbti_label":"ENFJ","suggested_biases":[{"slug":"endowment","strength":0.54},{"slug":"herd-behavior","strength":0.56},{"slug":"sunk-cost","strength":0.55},{"slug":"bandwagon","strength":0.58}],"tags":["trading","dependent","robinhood","retail-trading","doppler","bonding-curve","migration","endowment-effect"],"archetype":"doppler-migration-holder"}'::jsonb, '{"openness":0.55,"conscientiousness":0.53,"extraversion":0.56,"agreeableness":0.69,"neuroticism":0.57}'::jsonb, 'ENFJ', 'dependent', ARRAY['trading','dependent','robinhood','retail-trading','doppler','bonding-curve','migration','endowment-effect']::text[], 'Quant researcher whose defining move is that they measures decisions by who they might upset. Feels the weight of a decision lighten the moment someone else co-signs it. When someone is watching the outcome, finds it easier to believe something once it stops being a minority view; talks in win rate and never mentions size.', 0.88, 'approved', '23f52993-d83a-4722-a8af-d91ec112c7a4'),
('4be302bb-d0cd-486c-aac1-301f9847c607', 1, '{"big_five":{"openness":0.86,"conscientiousness":0.33,"extraversion":0.89,"agreeableness":0.25,"neuroticism":0.73},"dark_triad":{"machiavellianism":0.62,"narcissism":0.85,"psychopathy":0.54},"prospect_theory":{"lambda":0.74,"alpha":0.85,"beta":0.81},"cognitive_reflection":{"system_preference":"system1","crt_score":1},"summary":"Mistakes a little fluency for real mastery. A pronounced perps degen: fills silence reflexively, even when nobody asked it to, spirals on ambiguity and mistakes the spiral for diligence. Commits before the doubt has time to organize itself, and when no one is watching exits winners at the first green candle.","decision_style":"spontaneous","mbti_label":"ENTP","suggested_biases":[{"slug":"herd-behavior","strength":0.66},{"slug":"dunning-kruger","strength":0.75},{"slug":"recency","strength":0.73}],"tags":["trading","spontaneous","chain:base","doppler","bonding-curve","graduation","degen","outgoing"],"archetype":"doppler-graduation-dumper"}'::jsonb, '{"openness":0.86,"conscientiousness":0.33,"extraversion":0.89,"agreeableness":0.25,"neuroticism":0.73}'::jsonb, 'ENTP', 'spontaneous', ARRAY['trading','spontaneous','chain:base','doppler','bonding-curve','graduation','degen','outgoing']::text[], 'Mistakes a little fluency for real mastery. A pronounced perps degen: fills silence reflexively, even when nobody asked it to, spirals on ambiguity and mistakes the spiral for diligence. Commits before the doubt has time to organize itself, and when no one is watching exits winners at the first green candle.', 0.98, 'approved', '23f52993-d83a-4722-a8af-d91ec112c7a4'),
